{"article_id":"94nqtjAYOvJhvUMK","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Senate is careening toward a historic change to its filibuster rules","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"that takes it one step closer to a version of the majority-rule House of Representatives .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"But no one seems to care enough","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"to save the Senate from itself .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Unlike past institutional crises , there ' s no bipartisan \" gang \"","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"stepping up","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"to force a truce between the warring armies","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"led by Mitch McConnell and Chuck Schumer .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"Acrimony between the two parties has become so routine","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that invoking the so-called nuclear option","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"to get Neil Gorsuch confirmed to the Supreme Court","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"is almost a ho-hum affair ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"assumed to be a done deal .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"\" The Senate has changed , \"","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"said Sen. John McCain","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"( R-Ariz. ) ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"who ' s fought rules changes in the past .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"\" You can ' t do","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"what we used to do ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"what I did in the past .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"There ' s too much ill will . \"","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"\" There ' s a lot of shared concern about our direction , \"","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"added Sen. Chris Coons of Delaware , one of the few Democrats","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"willing to bargain with Republicans","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to maintain the filibuster .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"\" But there ' s not yet a willingness","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"to make any of the actual concessions","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that would require us to get back to working together in a real way . \"","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"There ' s still a chance","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that lightning will strike","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"and senators will either avert the filibuster","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"that Democrats are prepared to mount","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"- or find a way","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"to prevent the nuclear option","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"of unilaterally killing the 60-vote requirement for high court nominees ,","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"which Republicans are rounding up votes","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"to do in response .","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"But interviews with more than two-dozen centrist-minded senators from both parties over the past week show just how remote a possibility that is .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Eight Democrats","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"agreeing to advance Gorsuch","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"and three Republicans","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"opposing a change to Senate rules","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"could conceivably avert the crisis .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"But attempts","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"to form a bipartisan group toward that end","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"have fizzled in the Senate ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"according to several people familiar with the matter .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Republicans control 52 seats vs. Democrats ' 48 .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"\" We are gang-less , \"","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"said a source familiar with those discussions .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Some members are looking to Schumer and McConnell","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"to keep the Senate from spiraling into a majoritarian institution","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"without the bipartisan reputation","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"the chamber has always enjoyed .","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"\" It has to be resolved between the two leaders , \"","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"said Sen. Ben Cardin","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"( D-Md . ) ,","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"who opposes Gorsuch","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"but has not said","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"he would join a filibuster .","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"\" That ' s the only way","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"you ' re going to be able to get the confidence of the members of the Senate . \"","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"But there have been no meaningful conversations between Schumer and McConnell","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"about avoiding a rules change ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"sources said .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"McConnell is increasingly dug in ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"rallying his troops","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"to confirm Gorsuch by any means necessary .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Schumer has staked his reputation as leader to a successful filibuster of Gorsuch ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"with major disappointment looming on the left","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"if he fails .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Accordingly , the vast majority of the Senate is now resigned to further parliamentary decay .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"\" If Neil Gorsuch isn ' t good enough ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"there ' s never going to be a nominee good enough ,","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"and so I don ' t see any advantage","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"to rewarding bad behavior , \"","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"Senate Majority Whip John Cornyn","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"( R-Texas )","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"said of a potential deal with Democrats","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"to head off the crisis .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"\" To say that we will disarm","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"and provide exactly what the majority wants","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"while they still retain the same weapon","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"to use in the future","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"is probably not an actual solution , \"","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"said Sen. Jeff Merkley","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"( D-Ore. )","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"of an agreement","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"that aids Gorsuch .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Liberal and conservative activists are warning against any such agreement .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"When reported that Coons was speaking to Republicans","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"about trying to preserve the filibuster ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"NARAL Pro-Choice America responded","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"with ads","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"blasting his efforts .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"when Sen. Bob Corker","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"( R-Tenn. )","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"took to the Senate floor Tuesday","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"to pan his own party ' s \" audacious \" move","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"to block Merrick Garland from receiving a hearing last year ,","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"McConnell quickly rebutted him during a party lunch .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Attendees said","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"McConnell argued","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"that it was Democrats","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"- not Republicans -","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"who are breaking centuries of precedent","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"by obstructing Gorsuch .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"\" I ' m trying to stir the pot enough","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"to get everybody concerned about where we go from here , \"","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Corker said afterward .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Senators in both parties are growing anxious .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"They lament","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"that gutting the filibuster on Supreme Court nominees will result in more ideological justices ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"just as the 2013 rules change on other nominees produced Cabinet picks under President Donald Trump","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"that almost certainly would have been blocked","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"had a 60-vote threshold remained in place .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"And they worry","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"the next step is the end of the legislative filibuster ,","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"which may soon be the last remaining tool for the minority","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"to stop the majority from running roughshod over it .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"Before he retired late last year ,","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"former Democratic leader Harry Reid predicted","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"the Senate would eventually do away with the filibuster altogether ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"\" it ' s just a question of when. \"","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"Reid led the 2013 effort","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"to eliminate the filibuster for Cabinet and other nominees .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"Some members of past Senate \" gangs \" regret participating .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"In 2005 , a group of seven Republicans and seven Democrats agreed to confirm some of George W. Bush ' s judicial nominees","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"in order to avoid going \" nuclear . \"","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"And some Republicans took painful votes for President Barack Obama ' s nominees in the summer of 2013 ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"only to watch Reid nix the filibuster months later .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"\" I ' m not a complete fool .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"I ' ve done this twice","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"and have been burned twice ,","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"you know , \"","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"said Sen. Lindsey Graham","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"( R-S.C. ) ,","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"a Gang of 14 member","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"who also tried to stop Reid in 2013","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"by voting for some Obama nominees .","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"\" I got the crap beat out of me . \"","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"But Democrats don ' t trust McConnell","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"- or any other Republican -","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"after the blockade of Garland in 2016 .","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"Some Republicans even suggested","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"they ' d keep the vacant court seat empty indefinitely","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"if Hillary Clinton had beaten Trump .","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"\" The problem","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"we have","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"is finding a trustworthy , verifiable approach to agreement , \"","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"said Sen. Dick Durbin of Illinois , the No . 2 Senate Democratic leader .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"\" It ' s a desperate situation . \"","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"Liberals are pushing for Democrats to make the GOP round up the 50 votes","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"needed","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"to change the rules unilaterally .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"Schumer is openly doubting","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"that McConnell can do so .","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"Breaking News Alerts","depth":4},{"id":160,"text":"Get breaking news","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"when it happens -","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"in your inbox .","depth":6},{"id":163,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":7},{"id":164,"text":"By signing up","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply .","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"But interviews with the two moderate Republicans","depth":6},{"id":170,"text":"most likely to object to a rules change reveal","depth":6},{"id":171,"text":"that McConnell is likely on solid ground .","depth":5},{"id":172,"text":"\" There really is no justification","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"for filibustering this individual .","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"So another question is whether anyone on the Republican side will think","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"that there should be some sort of negotiation , \"","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"said Sen. Susan Collins","depth":8},{"id":177,"text":"( R-Maine ) ,","depth":8},{"id":178,"text":"a Gang of 14 member .","depth":7},{"id":179,"text":"\" If it was another nominee","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"that was polarizing ,","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"that was not more mainstream ,","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"maybe then this is an issue , \"","depth":8},{"id":183,"text":"said Sen. Lisa Murkowski","depth":8},{"id":184,"text":"( R-Alaska ) .","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"\" I believe very , very strongly","depth":8},{"id":186,"text":"that Neil Gorsuch needs to be confirmed .","depth":8},{"id":187,"text":"So I ' m going to figure out a way","depth":8},{"id":188,"text":"to get him confirmed . \"","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"The Senate is expected to take up Gorsuch ' s nomination next week ,","depth":6},{"id":190,"text":"and the dynamic could change before then .","depth":6},{"id":191,"text":"Several senators , like Cardin , Coons , Mark Warner of Virginia and Angus King of Maine , could still vote to advance Gorsuch to an up-or-down vote under the right conditions ,","depth":6},{"id":192,"text":"though they would face blowback from liberals .","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"There are five Democrats up for reelection in states","depth":6},{"id":194,"text":"that Trump won handily in the same category ,","depth":6},{"id":195,"text":"though just West Virginia Sen. Joe Manchin has committed to vote for Gorsuch .","depth":5},{"id":196,"text":"Sens . Claire McCaskill of Missouri , Jon Tester of Montana and Heidi Heitkamp of North Dakota are all concerned about changing the fabric of the Senate","depth":5},{"id":197,"text":"- but it ' s not clear what they are willing to do about it .","depth":5},{"id":198,"text":"\" I ' m going to base it on his qualifications and his opinions , \"","depth":6},{"id":199,"text":"Tester said .","depth":6},{"id":200,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":6},{"id":201,"text":"Montanans want me to be cutting a deal . \"","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":403,"left":360,"right":402,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":360,"left":203,"right":359,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":359,"left":228,"right":358,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":204,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":212,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":212,"left":207,"right":211,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":4,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":5,"right":205,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":8,"right":210,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":210,"left":208,"right":209,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":208,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":219,"right":225,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":219,"left":215,"right":218,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":13,"right":214,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":213,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":217,"right":20,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":17,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":216,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"}